03/11/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- KFOR Commander General Markus Bentler says he sees no external threats against Kosovo.
"The security situation in the region in general is satisfactory.
I don't see any threats from the outside.
This is good news for all citizens of Kosovo," Bentler said in an interview with the Pristina-based newspaper Koha Ditore on Tuesday (November 3rd).
He urged members of the public to look to the future with hope.
As for the reduction of KFOR troops, Bentler said that about 10,000 peacekeepers will continue to support security.
(Koha Ditore, Kohavision, Telegrafi - 03/11/09)
